PROSOMA. Anterior eye row very recurved and posterior slightly procurved; prosoma dark yellow with large lateral black taints, median region and posterior slope yellow, contoured by black lines (
Fig. 3A– B
). Chelicerae dark yellow with black stains, endites and labium black, sternum black with a median yellow taint.

OPISTHOSOMA. Predominantly dark-yellow, black on the back of the abdominal projections and on the sides, rough surfaced and slightly concave on the anterior border (
Fig. 3A–B
).
